##Guardian angels, each giving his own strength

Work together to tide over difficulties

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Three weeks after the city was shut down, new cases of pneumonia continue to rise across the country.

All people are looking forward to the inflection point, countless angels in white still adhere to the first line in the fight against the epidemic, not a moment to relax. All sectors of society are also participating in the fight against the epidemic by various means.

During this time, warmth and kindness are often found. Viruses are ruthless. People are ruthless.

"Take off your suit. You're exhausted. "

On the front line of prevention and control of the epidemic in Hubei, numerous medical and nursing personnel have been fighting round the clock. They are fully armed. Due to wearing masks, goggles, protective clothing, isolation clothing, gloves and other layers of protection for a long time, coupled with the negative pressure Ward air-conditioning temperature, almost all the medical staff are hot forehead sweat.

In such a high-intensity body overdraw, out of the ward, many people feel "take off the protective clothing like a layer of skin" , the body of water loss has been nearly exhausted.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The guidelines for the prevention of COVID-19 pneumonia in the elderly, recently released by Zhong Nanshan's team, also recommend that people pay attention to reasonable eating habits, a balanced diet, drinking water regularly, maintaining a healthy lifestyle and improving their resistance. Therefore, many medical staff are constantly reminding their colleagues: to maintain a healthy life state, appropriate replenishment of water, or it is easy to collapse, but delay treatment of patients.

The shortage of medical staff, the shortage of epidemic prevention materials, every piece of news about Wuhan affects everyone's heart, and the most urgent problem to be solved at present is: How to Support Wuhan? How To support medical staff?

"You watch over everybody, I watch over you. "

After the outbreak of the epidemic, all walks of life have extended the hand of donations, donations, donations of medical supplies, supplies of living materials, for the fight against the virus to contribute their own strength.

Alibaba set up a 1 billion Yuan Special Fund for Medical Supplies; Midea Group donated all the appliances needed to Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital and Wuhan Leishenshan Hospital; SF express opened a free public welfare transportation channel for relief supplies; Local Master Kong staff in Wuhan Organized anti-epidemic Rescue Activities, for the Wuhan major hospitals to transport food supplies for daily life, to ensure the safety of medical staff drinking water.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the case of the "city closure" in Wuhan, the staff of local master health in Wuhan Spontaneously Collated Hospital information through various public channels and personal social resources, and called the major local hospitals to confirm what material assistance was urgently needed, do A good job of demand statistics. At the same time, the emergency anti-epidemic support action coordination meeting was convened to discuss the material donation plan and implementation plan. After the local staff received the news, have also given up their leave of absence, to apply to join the anti-epidemic support special action to.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hao Haibo, head of the Hubei Marketing Department of Master Kong Marketing Company, came forward immediately to contact the hospital with the team of volunteers from the early stage of demand, data collation, to the delivery and distribution, constantly busy for support operations. He, as a family member of the health care workers, particularly understands the hard work and difficulties of the health care workers in the rapidly evolving situation, and also understands that in high-risk and densely populated places such as hospitals, bottled water or water glasses can be exposed to the air for a long time, it's easy to get infected by flying droplets, and the instant water can greatly reduce the risk of cross-infection, allowing health care workers to have a more secure drinking environment.

But in fact, whether at home or on the road, we should pay attention to reasonable living habits and personal protective measures. A safe and healthy source of water is also essential to daily life. Recently, the Ministry of Ecology and environment issued an emergency monitoring plan for COVID-19 pneumonia, which calls for strengthening early warning monitoring of water quality in drinking water sources during the period of prevention and control of the epidemic, monitoring of epidemic prevention and control characteristic indexes such as residual chlorine and biological toxicity. Although chlorine can be added to water to kill bacteria and remove microorganisms in the water, but to more thoroughly eliminate residual chlorine, daily boiling water need to boil a few minutes more. If you want to pursue a more secure way of drinking water, you can also directly choose RO RO reverse osmosis technology filter water, can effectively filter out heavy metals and viruses in water, such packaging water is usually in line with the National Haccp System Certification, it's more convenient and reassuring to drink.

While the epidemic continues, there is no shortage of heartwarming stories to convince us that the dawn of victory lies ahead. Whether it's the angels in white fighting the plague on the front lines, or people from all walks of life on the front lines, or companies with social responsibilities, we all want to do our part to bring a little warmth to the cold winter. And we all believe that if we work together, do our best, disaster will be overcome, spring will come.
